5:
...Ugh. I can't get used to the floor
swaying.
7:
Hah... There's nothing to do. No pirates
to fend off. No monsters to take down.
10:
You're making it sound like you WANT
something to attack us.
13:
Yeah, I could go for a good brawl. So
much for the high seas being full of
danger and excitement... It's too quiet.
16:
Oh, c'mon. It's nice having a little peace
and quiet. If you're bored, you can
come fish with me.
18: I bet you're a big fan of fish, right?
24:
I dunno. Cats like fish, so I thought
maybe you would too.
28:
I'm a TIGER, not a cat... Besides, the
desert isn't exactly known for its
seafood. I don't have much of an
opinion on it.
31:
That means you don't DISLIKE fish,
though, right? Let's catch a whole
bunch, then! You've got a whole
ocean try!
36:
But... Heh, you're in a good mood.
What's got you so fired up?
39:
Haha, I still can't believe Marina
offered me a job as chief steward.
That's pretty big praise!
43:
You sure you don't want to take her up
on it? Takin' over the galley wouldn't be
a bad gig for you.
45:
Wouldn't you be better off gutting fish
than baddies? No risk of getting gutted
yourself.
48:
I DID get banged up pretty bad earlier,
huh? Thanks for looking after me.
51: I didn't look after you at all.
54:
Stella said you were pretty worried
about me though?
60:
Well, I'm all right now, and that's
what counts. Next time, I'll be sure to
ask you if I need help, so...
62:
You don't need to worry about me,
okay?
65:
I wasn't WORRIED about you or
anything, just... Oh, whatever.
Suit yourself.
68:
Reeeally now? You can act tough,
but I know you're just a big worrywar—
71:
WHOA?! Th-there's something on the
line! It feels like a big one!
75:
Phew! ...Huh? Oh... Oh, WOW,
Nimbus look! It's HUGE!
77:
I bet it'll make great soup! That'd be
easy on the people with hangovers too!
I'll go get this guy drained and ready!
81: Man, he sure is enjoin' himself...
85:
Ooh, is that—could it be?
Do I see a SMILE?
Cute little convo you had there, matey!
88: Q-quit flyin' in outta nowhere like that!
92:
Ahaha! Gotta keep you landlubbers
on yer toes.
95:
Aaanywho, so like, you got any plans
for the future? You know, aside from
bein' a big fat softie?
100:
Relaaax. Okay, so like, I was thinking
you'd TOTALLY make a great pirate,
huh? Y'know, once you get yer sea legs.
101:
ALSO, there are other beastfolk here
and stuff? You'd be right at home.
104:
Hah! Nice try.
Sorry, but I'm not interested.
116:
Don't worry, I'm not that serious about
the recruiting stuff, but hey—I'm a
pirate, matey! I say what I want!
117:
You should try it. Like, quit the macho
lone-wolf act and be honest with
yourself—and yer crew!
120:
Oh, shut it. ...If you want some of Alk's
fish, you'd better get a move on.
123:
Oh yeah! That thing was HUUUGE!
Winner winner fishie dinner!
128:
Never a quiet moment with these guys...
What do you think of 'em, Rolan?
132:
Ocean as far as the eye can see.
Wish you could've seen it too...
